---
title: Nectarine and Zucchini Panzanella with Toasted Crouton and White Wine Vinaigrette
description: What’s not to like about a salad that’s equal parts bread and veggies? This panzanella gets its gusto from thinly shaved zucchini, fresh mozzarella, and a juicy, sweet nectarine. Unlike most salads, this one is even better if made a few hours in advance. Just toss the arugula and mint in right before serving.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/nectarine-and-zucchini-panzanella-84c771e8.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/nectarine-and-zucchini-panzanella-4b04a828.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/nectarine-and-zucchini-panzanella-590c7d5cd56afa52ea3b9033
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 530 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 20 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 480 mg
servings: 2
time required: 30m
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Slice @demi-baguette{1} into ¾-inch cubes.

Toss baguette cubes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toast in oven until golden brown and crisp on outside but still tender in center, ~{8-10%minutes}, tossing halfway through. Set aside to cool.

Wash and dry all produce. Using a #vegetable peeler{}, shave @zucchini{1} lengthwise into long ribbons, rotating to shave all sides. Stop shaving once you reach the seedy core; discard core. Place ribbons in a #large bowl{}. Put in refrigerator to chill.

Halve, pit, and thinly slice @nectarine{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Pick @mint{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked from stems) from stems; discard stems. Thinly slice leaves.

> TIP: Give vinaigrette a taste. If it seems sharp, add another drizzle of olive oil.

In a #small bowl{}, combine shallot, @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, and a large drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

Remove bowl with zucchini from refrigerator. Add mozzarella, baguette cubes, mint, @arugula{2%ounce}, nectarine, and vinaigrette to bowl. Toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper. Divide mixture between plates, top with a large drizzle of olive oil, and serve.